HEADWORD: Shoebill
<hw>Shoe"bill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large African wading bird (<spn>Balaeniceps rex</spn>) allied to
the storks and herons, and remarkable for its enormous broad swollen
bill. It inhabits the valley of the White Nile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

